article_text: Under the Affordable Care Act, people get tax credits if they bought insurance on exchanges ‘established by the State.’ Florida and 36 other states didn’t set up an exchange. The tax credit is being challenged in a case before the U.S. Supreme Court.

article_metadata.title: Supreme Court challenge to Obamacare tax credits casts cloud over program’s future | Miami Herald
